jade.tools.ascml.repository
Class ModelManager

java.lang.Object
  jade.tools.ascml.repository.ModelManager

public class ModelManager
extends java.lang.Object

The ModelManager caches society- and agentType-models which have been loaded by using the loadModelByFileName-method (this is the only way for storing models into the repository). It implements methods for accessing the models already loaded as well as a method for load and create models out of a given xml-file. It uses the ModelConfiguration to load new models independent from the loader-implementation. todo: Use weak hashmap?!

getModelIndex

public ModelIndex getModelIndex()
Returns the Map, containing all the names, that were found during the autosearch-process.

Returns:
The HashMap containing all models, that were found. The key of this HashMap is the file-name of the model, the value either also the file-name or the name of the jar-file containg the model-file.

loadModelByFileName

public java.lang.Object loadModelByFileName(java.lang.Object modelIdentifier)
                                     throws ModelException,
                                            ResourceNotFoundException
Load a model (either AgentType or SocietyType) from the file-system. If the model has been loaded before, the reference to this model is returned, otherwise the model-object is created out of the description-file from the given source.

Parameters:
modelIdentifier - String pointing to the description file. In case the model is contained within a jar/zip-Archive, the name has to be in the following form: 'jarFile.[jar|zip]::modelFile.[agent|society].xml'. Note the '::' to separate the jarFile's name from the model-name !
Returns:
model-object containing all the information specified within the source. Either a SocietyTypeModel or an AgentTypeModel is returned.
Throws:
ModelException - is thrown when ... (toDo)

loadAgentTypeByName

public IAgentType loadAgentTypeByName(java.lang.String agentName,
                                      java.lang.String[] agentTypeNames,
                                      java.lang.String[] imports,
                                      java.lang.String basePackageName)
                               throws ModelException,
                                      ResourceNotFoundException
Load an AgentType-model from the ModelIndex or the file-system. If the model has been loaded before, the reference to this model is returned, otherwise the model-object is created out of the description-file from the given source. This method is used exclusivly by the ModelReferenceResolver.

Parameters:
agentName - The name of the AgentType (if not fully-qualified, make sure you specify agentTypeNames or imports
agentTypeNames - A list of fully-qualified AgentType-names; one of these should match the not-fully-qualified agentName
imports - A list of imports; if the agentName is not fully-qualified and also not found in the list of fully-qualified AgentType-names, the list of imports is used to construct possible fully-qualified names.
basePackageName - This package-name is used to construct a fully-qualified agentName if all the above stated methods of constructing a fq-name fail.
Returns:
AgentType-model containing all the information specified within the source.
Throws:
ModelException - is thrown when ... (toDo)
ResourceNotFoundException

rebuildModelIndex

public java.util.HashMap rebuildModelIndex()
When this method is called, the index, which contains all agent- and society- description-filenames is refreshed. The method may be called due to a change of the model-path or when files are added or deleted within this path. The 'searchRoots'-method scans the complete model-path for model-description-files and stores the name of the files found in a global HashMap.

Returns:
The HashMap containing all models, that were found. The key of this HashMap is the file-name of the model, the value either also the file-name or the name of the jar-file containg the model-file.
